== Preliminaries ==
<pre>setgcc gcc4</pre> Haiku uses GCC 2 by default, which is too old for OpenTTD.
<pre>installoptionalpackage mercurial</pre>
or subversion if you wish. Alternatively, Git is available from http://haikuware.com/directory/view-details/development/miscellaneous/git (untested).

== SDL ==
"installoptionalpackage sdlllibs" won't do (compiled with GCC 2). Use [http://haikuware.com/directory/view-details/development/class-libraries/sdlgamelibraries-gcc4 this] instead.
== zlib ==
<pre>wget http://zlib.net/zlib-1.2.7.tar.gz
tar xvfz zlib-1.2.7.tar.gz
cd zlib-1.2.7
configure --prefix=/boot/common && make install</pre>

There will be an error, simply do

<pre>gcc -shared -O3  -fPIC -DHAVE_HIDDEN -o libz.so.1.2.7 adler32.lo crc32.lo deflate.lo infback.lo inffast.lo inflate.lo inftrees.lo trees.lo zutil.lo compress.lo uncompr.lo gzclose.lo gzlib.lo gzread.lo gzwrite.lo
make install
cd ..</pre>

and everything will be fine. This is the same command that triggers the error, only without "-lc" on the end.

